==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Comprint
<hw>Com*print"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t. & i.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>To print together.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(O. Eng. Law)</fld> <def>To print surreptitiously a
work belonging to another.</def> <rj><au>E. Phillips.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Comprint</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Comprint
<hw>Com"print</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(O. Eng. Law)</fld>
<def>The surreptitious printing of another's copy or book; a work thus
printed.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Comprisal</ent>⟦br⟧
